data.chText: 高奏凯歌的；大获全胜的；巨大成功的
data.enText: very successful in a way that causes great satisfaction

data.chText: 他们在九月份的选举中大获全胜。
data.enText: They emerged triumphant in the September election.

data.chText: 欢欣鼓舞的；扬扬得意的；耀武扬威的
data.enText: showing great satisfaction or joy about a victory or success

tr: joyful and proud especially because of triumph or success
example: rejoicing crowds filled the streets on VJ Day

value.def: Someone who is triumphant has gained a victory or succeeded in something and feels very happy about it.

example.ex: Duncan and his triumphant soldiers celebrate their military victory…
example.tran: 邓肯和他那些欢欣鼓舞的士兵们庆祝他们取得了军事胜利。
上校的声音听上去万分得意。

example.ex: This trip was not like his first triumphant return home in 1990.
example.tran: 这趟行程不同于他 1990 年的首次衣锦还乡。

value.tran: (成功或获胜后)欢欣鼓舞的，狂喜的

example.tran: “我也是这样认为的，”埃维莉娜得意地说。

example.ex: They marched triumphantly into the capital.
example.tran: 他们怀着胜利的喜悦列队进入首都。
